A Rutted Road~
   A dirt road lies east and west of here. Ruts made by wagon's wheels
gouge the road to either side. The fields that lie to the north are
ill tended. Grass has overtaken parts of the nearest field and the
corn that is planted there are leaning with wilted brown leaves. To
the south it looks even worse. What might have once been a field is
now a tangle of brush and briars.
